3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour using a premium index based on the difference between perpetual and spot prices. The on-chain order book ensures transparent rate calculations without hidden adjustments. Funding payments occur at the top of each hour, with rates typically ranging from -0.01% to 0.01% per hour. The platform's sub-second finality enables real-time position adjustments for optimal funding capture."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TON","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON's integration with Telegram's ecosystem creates unique market dynamics that often result in funding rate inefficiencies. The token's large trading volume and active derivatives market across multiple exchanges provide consistent arbitrage opportunities. TON's price volatility during major Telegram announcements frequently generates extreme funding rates exceeding 0.05% hourly."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON/USDT funding rates on Hyperliquid have shown distinct patterns correlating with Telegram ecosystem developments and broader crypto market trends. During Q3 2024, average rates remained between -0.002% to 0.004% hourly, with significant spikes to 0.08% during major TON network updates. The 1-hour funding frequency creates more granular opportunities compared to 8-hour cycles on traditional CEXs. Weekend periods typically see reduced volatility in funding rates due to lower institutional trading activity. Major TON ecosystem announcements consistently produce funding rate anomalies lasting 2-4 hours."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid's hourly funding creates 24 potential arbitrage windows daily versus competitors' 3 cycles, significantly increasing profit opportunities. Cross-exchange arbitrage between Hyperliquid and Binance/OKX often yields 0.01-0.03% profit per funding period due to different calculation methodologies. The platform's 0.02% maker fee structure allows profitable arbitrage when funding differentials exceed 0.04% hourly. On-chain execution eliminates counterparty risk common in CEX arbitrage, though gas costs on Hyperliquid's L1 remain minimal at ~$0.01 per transaction. Long TON positions during positive funding periods have historically outperformed simple holding strategies by 2-4% annually."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"While Hyperliquid offers compelling funding arbitrage opportunities, several risks require careful management. The platform's newer status compared to established CEXs means less historical data for strategy backtesting and potential smart contract vulnerabilities. USDC-only settlement creates additional currency risk for traders preferring USDT exposure. TON's volatility can quickly erode funding profits through adverse price movements, particularly during 10%+ daily swings common in the token. The single-chain ecosystem limits hedging options compared to multi-chain alternatives, requiring more precise risk management strategies."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does Hyperliquid calculate TON/USDT funding rates?","answer":"Hyperliquid calculates and applies funding rates every hour for all perpetual contracts including TON/USDT. This creates 24 funding periods daily, significantly more than the typical 8-hour cycles used by most centralized exchanges."},{"question":"What makes TON funding arbitrage profitable on Hyperliquid?","answer":"TON's high volatility combined with Hyperliquid's hourly funding creates frequent rate disparities with other exchanges. The platform's low fees (0.02% maker) and on-chain transparency allow profitable arbitrage when funding differentials exceed 0.04% per hour."},{"question":"Can I hedge TON price risk while capturing funding rates?","answer":"Yes, traders can hedge TON exposure by taking opposite positions on other exchanges or using spot TON holdings. However, Hyperliquid's single-chain design limits native hedging options compared to multi-chain platforms, requiring external hedging strategies."},{"question":"What are the main risks of TON funding arbitrage on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Key risks include TON's high price volatility potentially overwhelming funding profits, Hyperliquid's newer platform status with limited track record, and USDC-only settlement creating currency exposure. Smart contract risks also exist given the platform's on-chain nature."}]}]
